# How to Calculate Dividend Capitalization? 
# Capitalized Dividends means Dividends due on the Preferred Shares pursuant to Section 1 that have been capitalized by adding the amount of the Dividends to the Stated Value of the Preferred Shares.print("===]  Calculation Current Ratio  [===")

dividendNextYear = float(input("Divident or Share next year : "))
currentSharePrice = float(input("Current Price Share : "))
dividendGrowthRate = float(input("Divident Growth Rate : "))

# calculate
costEquity = (dividendNextYear/currentSharePrice) + dividendGrowthRate
print("Divident Capitalization : ", costEquity)
